## Correctness
The new genre-literacy strategy library exists and covers all required genres (`ambient/drone/generative`, `minimalism`, `jazz`, `idm/electronic`, `classical/orchestral form`, `musique concrete/electroacoustic`, `spectral music`, `blues`, `world-music`, `post-rock/experimental`).

Selection APIs and arc-affinity logic are implemented, and tests for no missing required strategies, selection behavior, required fields, and affinity behavior are present. However, strategies are not yet integrated into the active composition/control path, so they currently do not influence form/harmony/rhythm/synthesis/arrangement/mix during generation despite existing definitions.

## Completeness
The acceptance criteria are partially complete:
- Library coverage: complete.
- Test coverage for strategy selection/affinity/required presence: complete.
- Hardening checks called out in prompt: largely implemented (see below).
- Integration into active pipeline where strategies can actually shape compositional decisions: incomplete (critical functional gap).

## Consistency
New module style is consistent with existing typed dataclass/enumeration patterns and test style in the project. Naming is coherent with existing conventions, but the new strategy layer is disconnected from runtime selection usage points, reducing functional consistency with runtime architecture.

## Security
No secrets or credentials were introduced. No unsafe command execution or external data flow was added in the changed scope.

## Quality
Automated tests for the touched surface are solid and run-to-pass for existing suite, including the requested command (`pytest tests/ -x`). The main quality gap is architectural wiring: strategy definitions exist but are not consumed in generation orchestration.

## Issues Found
- [ ] Blocking: Genre strategy library is not connected to active generation flow; there is no evidence that selected strategies affect form, harmony, rhythm, synthesis, arrangement, or mix in production composition paths.
- [x] Minor/Resolved: Recurring failure mode — `revise_score(...)` was not wired into composition/playback flow and is now integrated in `tracker_compiler.py` and `duet_composer.py`.
- [x] Minor/Resolved: Recurring failure mode — one-pass budget fields were computed but not applied in `tracker_solo_song`; enforcement hooks now exist and are used in event generation controls.
- [x] Minor/Resolved: Recurring failure mode — daemon path lacked identity bootstrap; `cypherclaw_daemon.py` now calls `bootstrap_identity()` during startup.

